# AddressSanitizer suppressions for helix-screen.
#
# Use with:
#   ASAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=tests/asan.supp:detect_leaks=0:abort_on_error=1:fast_unwind_on_malloc=0 \
#       ./build/pi-asan/bin/helix-screen
#
# Suppression syntax:
#   interceptor_via_lib:<library>     - silence reports inside a shared lib
#   interceptor_via_fun:<function>    - silence reports through a particular function
#   interceptor_name:<func>           - silence reports about a particular libc wrapper
#
# Be conservative — every suppression hides real bugs along with noise. Add a
# comment explaining WHY each entry is here so future readers can audit it.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LVGL image cache: holds decoded image buffers across object lifetimes by
# design. ASAN's leak detector flags these on shutdown; runtime reads from
# the cache are correct. Detect_leaks=0 in ASAN_OPTIONS already silences
# leaks; leave the LSAN block here in case someone re-enables leak detection.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
leak:lv_image_cache_*
leak:_lv_image_cache_*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# glibc gconv lazy locale init: opens locale modules on first use and never
# unloads them. Surfaces as "leaked" allocations from libdl on shutdown.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
leak:libgconv*
leak:__gconv_*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# libhv worker pools: thread-local buffers retained for the process lifetime.
# These are real (intentional) leaks but not actionable and obscure real
# findings during stress runs.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
leak:hv::EventLoopThreadPool*
leak:hv::HThreadPool*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Add real findings BELOW this line. Every real-bug suppression deserves a
# linked issue so we don't paper over recurring problems.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
